# Development Workflow

## Development Commands

### Core Commands
```bash
# Start development server
npm run dev

# Production build
npm run build

# Preview production build
npm run preview
```

### Code Quality
```bash
# Format code with Prettier
npx prettier --write .

# TypeScript type checking
npx tsc --noEmit

# Build validation (run before commits)
npm run build
```

## Build Process

### Static Site Generation
- Astro generates static HTML/CSS/JS
- Content collections processed at build time
- Social cards (OG images) generated via Satori
- RSS feed and sitemap auto-generated

### Performance Features
- Code splitting and lazy loading
- Image optimization (built-in Astro features)
- Critical CSS inlining
- Minimal JavaScript hydration

## Content Workflow

### Adding Blog Posts
1. Create `.md` or `.mdx` file in `src/content/posts/`
2. Add required frontmatter (title, published, tags)
3. Write content using Markdown/MDX features
4. Test locally with `npm run dev`
5. Build and validate with `npm run build`

### Adding Portfolio Items
1. Create `.md` file in `src/content/works/`
2. Use appropriate `type` field (work, oss, presentation, other)
3. Set `featured: true` for homepage display
4. Include external `link` if applicable

## Plugin System

### Custom Plugins (`src/plugins/`)
- [remark-admonitions.ts](mdc:src/plugins/remark-admonitions.ts) - Note/warning blocks
- [remark-gemoji.ts](mdc:src/plugins/remark-gemoji.ts) - Emoji shortcode support

### Content Processing Pipeline
1. Markdown/MDX parsing
2. Remark plugins (content transformation)
3. Rehype plugins (HTML transformation)
4. Syntax highlighting with Expressive Code
5. Math rendering with KaTeX

## Deployment Considerations

### Pre-deployment Checklist
- [ ] `npm run build` succeeds without errors
- [ ] TypeScript type checking passes
- [ ] Content validates against schemas
- [ ] Social cards generate properly
- [ ] Search index builds correctly

### Environment Requirements
- Node.js (latest LTS)
- Static hosting (Vercel, Netlify, etc.)
- No server-side runtime needed
